{
  "text": "Single-round infectivity assays were performed as described by [CITATION_1] . 293FT cells (Invitrogen) were transiently co-transfected with 8 Ag proviral DNA (pGMo, pGMofs-long, pGMofs-short or pGMofs-B*), 2 Ag of a murine retrovirus vector (SRaLluc) carrying a reporter gene coding for the firefly luciferase and 1 Ag of pcDNA3.1/hygro(+)/lacZ. The culture media were collected 48 h post-transfection. The h-galactosidase activity of the cell lysates was measured to normalize for variations in transfection efficiency, as described above in the luciferase assays section. Equivalent volumes (1 or 3 ml) of culture medium containing either the wild-type or the mutant reporter virus were used to infect NIH 3T3 cells during 1 h in presence of polybrene at 8 Ag/ml. Cells were trypsinized 36 h post-infection, pelleted and washed with PBS, lysed with 200 Al of the Culture Cell Lysis Reagent (Promega) and the infectivity of the viruses was assayed by measuring the luciferase activity in lysates (5 Al) of the infected cells, as described above.",
